The Murphy Oil USA, Inc - Meridian Terminal is located in Meridian, Mississippi.  The facility is an independent wholesale distributor of petroleum-based refined products.   Operation of these processes involves the use or handling of certain listed regulated substances as defined by the Environmental Protection Agency (EPA). Currently, the only regulated substances within a process in an amount above their threshold quantities are butane and isobutane which are stored in a pressurized bullet tank with a maximum rated capacity of 30,000 gallons or 145,800 pounds (lbs). Depending on facility operations, the tank contents are planned to be comprised of either butane or isobutane.   Butane and isobutane are used as seasonal blending components in gasoline.

The facility is committed to operating in a manner that is safe for the facility's workers, the public, and the environment. 



As part of this commitment, Murphy Oil USA, Inc. has established systems to ensure safe operation of the facility. The facility maintains a management system and associated policies, procedures, programs, and work practices that are related to RMP Prevention Program elements. This document is intended to satisfy the RMP requirements and to provide the public with a description of the risk management program at the facility in Meridian, Mississippi.



The Executive Summary includes an overview of the following elements:

-    Accidental release prevention and emergency response policies;

-    Facility and regulated substances;

-    Accidental release prevention program and chemical-specific prevention steps;

-    Five-year accident history;

-    Emergency response program; and 

-    Planned changes to improve safety



